### [2 Kings (2 Samuel) Chapter 21](../../../bib/kjv/sa2021.htm#001.md)

[2 Kings (2 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa2 21:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa2 21:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa2021.htm#001.md), The three years' famine for
the Gibeonites ceases, by hanging seven of Saul's sons; [Sa2
21:10](../../../bib/kjv/sa2021.htm#010.md), Rizpah's kindness unto the
dead; [Sa2 21:12](../../../bib/kjv/sa2021.htm#012.md), David buries the
bones of Saul and Jonathan in his father's sepulchre; [Sa2
21:15](../../../bib/kjv/sa2021.htm#015.md), Four battles against the
Philistines, wherein four valiants of David slay four giants.

